question_text: True or False - By April, about a quarter of the U.S. population was fully vaccinated.
True or False - By April, less than a quarter of the U.S. population was fully vaccinated.
True or False - By August, about half of the U.S. population was fully vaccinated.
True or False - By August, less than half of the U.S. population was fully vaccinated.
True or False - A greater percentage of the U.S. population became fully vaccinated in October than in May.
True or False - A greater percentage of the U.S. population became fully vaccinated in May than in October.
True or False - A smaller percentage of the U.S. population became fully vaccinated in September than in April.
True or False - A smaller percentage of the U.S. population became fully vaccinated in April than in September.
True or False - From August to October, about half of the U.S. population became fully vaccinated.
True or False - From August to October, less than 10 percent of the U.S. population became fully vaccinated.
